The paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML) techniques to leverage eye-tracking data in a dependency parser. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses multitask learning and RNNs, which are common techniques in the sub-categories cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper deals with visual data (eye-tracking), which could place it in the sub-category cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper discusses the potential impact on human-computer interaction, which could place it in the sub-category cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
